---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="How to Play Scrabble — Beginner's Guide"
  description="Step-by-step beginner guide to playing Scrabble. Learn setup, turns, scoring, and winning strategies. Free guide, no signup needed."
  keywords="how to play scrabble, scrabble rules beginner, learn scrabble, scrabble for beginners, scrabble setup, play scrabble step by step"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "How to Play Scrabble: A Step-by-Step Beginner's Guide",
    "description": "Step-by-step beginner guide to playing Scrabble. Learn setup, turns, scoring, and winning strategies.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-12",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/how-to-play-scrabble" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do you start a game of Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Each player draws 7 tiles from the bag. Players then draw one tile each to determine who goes first (closest to A wins). The first player forms a word that covers the centre star square, which acts as a double word score." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you use two-letter words in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, two-letter words are legal and essential in Scrabble strategy. There are over 100 valid two-letter words in the official SOWPODS dictionary, including QI, ZA, XI, and XU." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What happens when you use all 7 tiles in one turn?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Playing all 7 tiles in a single turn is called a 'bingo' and earns a 50-point bonus on top of the word's regular score. This is one of the most powerful moves in Scrabble." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Beginner Guides</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">How to Play Scrabble: A Step-by-Step Beginner's Guide</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-12">June 12, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Ready to learn Scrabble? This guide walks you through everything from setting up the board to playing your first word. Scrabble might look complicated at first glance, but the core rules are simple. Within one game, you'll have the hang of it — and within a few, you'll be spotting opportunities your opponents miss entirely.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 ESSENTIALS</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">LEARN IN 8 STEPS</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">Setup → First Word → Build → Score → Blanks → Exchange → Challenge → End</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Everything you need to play your first game confidently. The rules are simple — mastery comes from the strategy you layer on top.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat Strip: Game Basics -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">15×15</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Board grid</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">100</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter tiles</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">7</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles per rack</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">2-4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Players</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What You Need</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">A standard Scrabble set includes a game board (15×15 grid), 100 letter tiles, a tile bag, and tile racks for each player. You'll need 2-4 players. If you don't have a physical set, numerous online versions replicate the experience — and our <a href="/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">free word finder</a> can help you practise finding words from any set of letters in realtime.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Step 1: Setting Up</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Place the board on a flat surface. Put all 100 tiles face-down in the bag and mix them thoroughly. Each player draws a tile — the player whose tile is closest to the letter A goes first. Return those tiles and remix.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Each player then draws 7 tiles from the bag and places them on their rack, hidden from other players. You should always have 7 tiles on your rack (until the bag is empty).</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Step 2: The First Word</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">The first player forms a word using their tiles and places it on the board so that one tile covers the centre star (★). This star acts as a double word score, so the first word automatically gets its total doubled.</p>

      <!-- Insight Callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 First Word Tip</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The first word is <span class="text-white font-medium">automatically doubled</span>. A 5-letter word scoring 12 base points becomes 24 on the opening move. Aim for the longest, highest-scoring word you can find — it's free value.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-300">Words must be placed either horizontally (left to right) or vertically (top to bottom) — never diagonally. The first word must be at least 2 letters long. After placing, announce your score, draw tiles to refill to 7, and pass the turn.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Step 3: Building On the Board</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">From the second turn onward, every word must connect to at least one existing tile on the board — just like a crossword puzzle. You can:</p>

      <!-- Card Grid: 3 Ways to Build -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Extend a word:</span> Add letters to the beginning or end of an existing word (turning "CAT" into "CATS" or "SCAT").</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Branch off:</span> Place a new word perpendicular to an existing one, sharing a letter at the intersection.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play parallel:</span> Place a word alongside an existing one, as long as every adjacent tile combination forms a valid word.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-300">Every new letter combination created in a single turn must be a valid word. If your word creates two-letter combinations where it touches existing tiles, those must also be legitimate words.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Step 4: Scoring Your Words</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Each tile has a point value printed on it. To score a word, add up the values of all tiles in the word. Then apply any premium squares:</p>

      <!-- Premium Squares Cards -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Letter Multipliers</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400"><strong>DL (Light Blue):</strong> Doubles one tile's value. <strong>TL (Dark Blue):</strong> Triples one tile's value. Applied first, before word multipliers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Word Multipliers</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400"><strong>DW (Pink):</strong> Doubles entire word score. <strong>TW (Red):</strong> Triples entire word score. Applied after all letter values are totalled.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-300">Premium squares only count on the turn the tile is first placed on them. For a deeper dive, read our <a href="/blog/scrabble-scoring-guide/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">complete scoring guide</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Step 5: Using Blank Tiles</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">The two blank tiles are wildcards. A blank can represent any letter you choose when you play it. However, blanks are worth zero points. Once placed, a blank remains that letter for the rest of the game.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Blanks are extremely valuable despite being worthless in points because they let you form high-scoring words or achieve the 50-point bingo bonus (using all 7 tiles in one turn).</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Step 6: Exchanging Tiles</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">If you're stuck with a terrible rack, you can exchange tiles instead of playing a word. Place the tiles you want to exchange face-down, draw the same number of new tiles from the bag, then return your old tiles. This uses your entire turn — you score zero points — but it saves you from being stuck.</p>

      <!-- Warning Callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">⚠️ Exchange Rules</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">You can exchange 1 to all 7 tiles, but <span class="text-white font-medium">only when at least 7 tiles remain in the bag</span>. Once the bag has fewer than 7 tiles, exchanging is no longer allowed — you must play or pass.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Step 7: Challenging Words</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">If you think an opponent played an invalid word, you can challenge it. The challenged word is looked up in the official dictionary. If invalid, the player removes their tiles and loses their turn. Challenge rules vary — casual play often uses free challenges, while competitive play penalises failed challengers.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Step 8: Ending the Game</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">The game ends when one player uses all their tiles with an empty bag (they get bonus points equal to opponents' remaining tile values), or when all players pass consecutively. Unplayed tiles are subtracted from each player's score. Highest total wins.</p>

      <!-- Numbered Steps Summary -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Turn Summary (Every Turn)</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Play a word</span> (or exchange tiles, or pass)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Score the word</span> — add tile values + apply premium squares</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Draw tiles</span> from the bag to refill your rack to 7</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Pass the turn</span> to the next player</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Quick Tips for Beginners</h2>

      <!-- Purple Strategy Tips -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Learn two-letter words:</span> They're essential for parallel plays and scoring in tight spaces. QI, ZA, XI, XU, and JO are game-changers worth 9-11 points each.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Balance your rack:</span> Keep a mix of vowels and consonants. A rack full of one type limits your options dramatically.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Aim for premium squares:</span> A 3-point tile on a TLS scores 9 points instead of 3. A whole word on TWS triples everything.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Don't open triple words for opponents:</span> Be careful about placing tiles adjacent to TWS unless you're using them yourself.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Inline Cross-Links -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Next Steps</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/beginner-scrabble-strategy/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Beginner Strategy — 10 tips to start winning once you know the rules</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-scoring-guide/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
